Hey, not sure if this has been reported by anyone else (I couldn't find anything) but i cant see any of the new buildings in the map screen i can see all the icons and selects them for info and such (they are all black, but thats a known active texture management thing, right?) but when i select a site to spawn from in a craft, i spawn and there is no building! I've tested it on quite a few now, ones i know should have buildings. Its really annoying, does anyone have a idea whats causing it?

And a couple other small mods...

1 - Check the subdirectory structure of both Kerbal Konstructs and KerbinSide has been retained in GameData the same as it is in the zips. Don't arbitarily decide to re-organise the directory structures of either mod.

2 - Check if there's a duplicate KerbalKonstructs.dll somewhere in GameData. I've had reports of CKAN misinstalling the KK dll.

3 - If you are using Active Texture Management, go to the OP of the Kerbal Konstructs thread where you will find links to config files to use with ATM.

4 - Update Kerbal Konstructs. KK is often well ahead of the version that goes out with the last KerbinSide.

If all of that doesn't help, back up your saves. Do a clean install Kerbal Konstructs and KerbinSide.

If that doesn't help, do a clean install of all your mods.

If that doesn't help, do a clean install of KSP and all your mods.

If that doesn't help, you're in the Matrix. There is no spoon.
